Irwin D. Groak, appellant, v. Union Bank of Chicago et al., appellees.Gen. No. 24,158.Bill for accounting and to enjoin proceedings under judgment. Dismissal for want of equity. Appeal from the Circuit Court of Cook county; the Hon. Merritt W. Pinckney, Judge, presiding. Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the March term, 1918.Opinion filed April 30, 1919.Richard S. Folsom, for appellant. Morrill, Shannon & Triska, for appellee Swedish-Ameriean Tel. Mfg. Co.; North Allen, of counsel. Mr. Justice Taylor delivered the opinion of the court.

Affirmed.
